text: The VFW-Fokker 614 is a West German and Dutch airliner manufactured by VFW- Fokker. It is a twin-turbojet aircraft. It is holds certain significance as its two engines are on pylons above the wing. VFW-Fokker 614 can carry between 40 and 44 passengers. It was used by airlines in Denmark, France, and Germany until 2007. German Air Force, the Luftwaffe, also used this aircraft for speed liaisons and VIP transport. == Images: == File:VFW-614 Air Alsace Basle - 15 Oct 1977.jpg|Side view of the aircraft File:Vfw 614 01.jpg|Over wing mounted engine File:Cimber Air VFW-614.jpg|The aircraft in service at Cimber Category:Civil aircraft Category:German military aircraft
